# Build context for testkit/Dockerfile is the testkit/ directory
# itself, not the project root, so the docker context is already tiny.
# This file just keeps in-place artifacts out:
#   - CAs/, CustomCAs/ are populated by testkit at build time and
#     copied in explicitly via COPY in the Dockerfile; without ignoring
#     them here, an out-of-date local copy could shadow what testkit
#     freshly drops.
# In practice testkit always re-populates them before building, so
# this is belt-and-suspenders.
*.pyc
__pycache__/
